---
/**
 * Persona-Inspector — INTERNAL-ONLY directory of role-string slugs,
 * functional roles, activation status, persona-hash-pin constants,
 * and constituting ADRs.
 *
 * NOT A MARKETING SURFACE. The page is intentionally internal-only:
 *
 *   - `<Base noindex>` emits `<meta name="robots" content="noindex,
 *     nofollow">` and suppresses canonical / OpenGraph / Twitter /
 *     hreflang / JSON-LD tags so search engines and social previews
 *     do not index this URL.
 *   - The page renders role-string slugs only — never clear-names.
 *     Brand-Guide §9 (blocklist path) applies to every public-Astro
 *     surface, including pages that are nominally "internal".
 *   - The page does NOT render a count statement ("we are N
 *     personas"). The directory shows individual cards; any count
 *     signal is opaque (ADR ids, not totals).
 *
 * Audience (per F3 = intern-only Phase-0 decision, Mira-Antwort
 * 2026-05-07):
 *   - Wakir-team reviewers checking persona configuration,
 *     persona-hash-pin alignment with the persona-engine pin pack,
 *     and ADR cross-references.
 *   - Internal audit (`internal-audit` role) cross-referencing
 *     activation ADRs against the wave-3 cohort.
 *   - HR (`hr` role) verifying the activation-state surface against
 *     the persona files.
 *
 * NOT for: external reviewers, marketing audience, third-party
 * compliance auditors. Those audiences read `/verifier/`,
 * `/audit-trail/`, and the position papers.
 *
 * Cross-Review-Hooks:
 *   - Comms Zone-G: NOT triggered for an internal-only page in the
 *     same way as marketing surfaces are. Brand-Guide §9 still
 *     applies (role-strings only, no count). A Zone-G heads-up
 *     remains good practice.
 *   - Persona-engine schema sync (`persona-engine-eng` role): the
 *     hash-pin constant name shown on each card is a downstream
 *     consumer expectation; if the persona-engine renames the
 *     constant, this surface needs a paired edit.
 *
 * Provisional content. The persona-engine does not yet emit a JSON
 * directory that this page can consume directly; the data lives in
 * `src/data/wakir-persona-inspector-sample.ts` as a build-time
 * inlined fixture. When the persona-engine surface lands a real
 * directory export, this page switches over.
 */
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import PersonaInspectorEntry from "../components/PersonaInspectorEntry.astro";
import { samplePersonaInspector } from "../data/wakir-persona-inspector-sample";

const title = "Persona inspector (internal)";
const description =
  "Internal-only role-string directory: slug, functional role, activation status, persona-hash-pin constant, constituting ADR.";
---

<Base title={title} description={description} noindex>
  <article class="essay">
    <header class="essay__header">
      <h1 class="essay__title">Persona inspector</h1>
      <p class="essay__lead">
        An internal read-only view of the role-string directory. Each
        card lists the inter-agent slug, the functional role, the
        activation status, the persona-hash-pin constant the
        persona-engine pins against, and the constituting ADR.
      </p>
      <p class="wakir-persona-inspector__internal-banner" role="note">
        <strong>Internal-only surface.</strong> This page is not part
        of the marketing surface; the response sets
        <code>noindex,nofollow</code>. Reviewers reading externally
        should use <a href="/verifier/">the verifier page</a> or
        <a href="/audit-trail/">the audit trail</a> instead.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="essay__body">
      <h2>How to read a card</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Slug.</strong> The single-word inter-agent
          identifier. The same slug used in <code>subagent_type=…</code>,
          in NATS subject names, and in cross-review references.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Role.</strong> The functional role descriptor in the
          form used across the org (<code>dev-engineering</code>,
          <code>wirelang-eng</code>, <code>frontend-eng</code>). Plain
          functional descriptor; not a clear-name.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Domain.</strong> One sentence describing what the
          role owns. Read off the persona files; kept short so a
          reviewer can scan the directory at glance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Activation status.</strong> <code>active</code> when
          the role is delivering work today;
          <code>in&nbsp;activation</code> when the persona file is
          approved (ADR landed) but the agent has not yet been spawned
          for productive output. Wave-3 activations carry the
          <code>in&nbsp;activation</code> status until first delivery
          lands.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Hash-pin constant.</strong> The named export of the
          persona-engine that pins the canonical-subset SHA-256 of the
          persona-definition file. The raw hash lives on
          <a href="/audit-trail/">the audit trail</a>; the constant
          name on each card keeps the inspector readable without
          duplicating a hash that might drift across surfaces.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Constituting ADR.</strong> The architecture decision
          that activated the role. Reviewers cross-reference governance
          via these ADR ids.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Directory</h2>

      <p>
        Cards are listed in the natural ADR-arrival order so the
        directory reads the way the org grew, not alphabetically.
      </p>

      <ol class="wakir-persona-inspector-list" aria-label="Persona directory">
        {samplePersonaInspector.map((entry) => (
          <li class="wakir-persona-inspector-list__item">
            <PersonaInspectorEntry entry={entry} />
          </li>
        ))}
      </ol>

      <h2>What is not here yet</h2>

      <p>
        This is a read-only structural sketch. It does not yet support
        filtering by status, search by slug, or per-card expansion to
        show the full persona-definition body. The persona-engine does
        not yet emit a JSON directory export that this page can consume
        directly; the data above is build-time inlined from
        <code>src/data/wakir-persona-inspector-sample.ts</code> and
        mirrors <code>scripts/lib/wakir-personas.txt</code> (single
        source of truth for the role-string directory). When the
        persona-engine surface lands a real directory export, this
        page switches over. Until then, the cards above are real but
        partial.
      </p>

      <h2>Why this page is internal-only</h2>

      <p>
        Brand-Guide §9 keeps the role-string directory off public
        surfaces. A public version of this directory is therefore not
        on the roadmap. The inspector ships internal-only:
        <code>noindex,nofollow</code>, no canonical, no OpenGraph, no
        hreflang. Outside readers use
        <a href="/verifier/">the verifier</a> and
        <a href="/audit-trail/">the audit trail</a> — both render
        substance (Bitcoin anchors, pin packs, persona-hash pins)
        without exposing the role-string directory.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
